State calculated a rate of 14.1 percent without the modifier limitation. State believes the rate is underestimated because some providers do not bill for CPT code 96110. State conducted an internal validation of the data.
Source: Mathematica analysis of MACPro reports for the FFY 2017 reporting cycle as of November 1, 2018.

State Specific Comments: Rate includes PCCM and managed care populations (5 MCOs), representing 76 percent of the population. Rate excludes FFS population, representing 24 percent of the population. State requires that providers offer a behavioral health screening to all children ages 0 to 21 using a standardized screening tool selected from a state-approved list of screening tools, but the list includes global and non-global screenings. As a result, the state's method deviates from Core Set specifications because it cannot differentiate between global and non-global screenings. Based on previous studies, the state believes that global screening tools account for a large percentage of the conducted screenings.

State Specific Comments: Medicaid rates include managed care population (4 MCOs), representing 85 percent of the population. Rates exclude FFS population, representing 15 percent of the population. Rate Definition: Percentage at Elevated Risk of Dental Caries (Moderate or High Risk) who Received a Sealant on a Permanent First Molar Tooth: Ages 6-9
State Specific Comments: Rate includes FFS and managed care populations (5 MCOs).
Source: Mathematica analysis of MACPro reports for the FFY 2017 reporting cycle as of November 1, 2018.

Domain: Maternal and Perinatal Health
Measure Name: Prenatal and Postpartum Care: Timeliness of Prenatal Care
Rate Definition: Percentage of Women Delivering a Live Birth with a Prenatal Care Visit in the First Trimester or within 42 Days of Medicaid/CHIP Enrollment
State Specific Comments: Rate includes FFS, PCCM, and managed care populations (5 MCOs). State used vital records to determine first trimester prenatal care, and the measure specification claim codes to identify prenatal care records within 42 days of enrollment to capture prenatal care initiation during first trimester for cases where encounter data may not be complete. Denominator excludes records with missing birth certificate information about when prenatal care began that also had no prenatal care claims within 42 days of Medicaid enrollment (about 4.7 percent of births). Rate was calculated using the 15th of the month as the eligibility start date. Rate includes the following taxonomy codes as service provider to identify prenatal care and not emergent care: Family Medicine, General Practice, OB/GYN, Obstetric, Midwife, Lay Midwife, Advanced Practice Midwife, Family Nurse Practitioner, OB/GYN Nurse Practitioner, Primary Care Nurse Practitioner, and Physician Assistant.
Source: Mathematica analysis of MACPro reports for the FFY 2017 reporting cycle as of November 1, 2018.

Domain: Behavioral Health Care
Measure Name: Use of Multiple Concurrent Antipsychotics in Children and Adolescents: Ages 1-17
Rate Definition: Percentage on Two or More Concurrent Antipsychotic Medications: Ages 1-17
State Specific Comments: Medicaid rate includes managed care population (4 MCOs), representing 85 percent of the population. Rate excludes FFS population, representing 15 percent of the population. MCO rates were audited by certified HEDIS auditors.
Source: Mathematica analysis of MACPro reports for the FFY 2017 reporting cycle as of November 1, 2018.

Domain: Care of Acute and Chronic Conditions
Measure Name: Medication Management for People with Asthma: Ages 5-20
Rate Definition: Percentage with Persistent Asthma who were Dispensed Appropriate Medication and Remained on Medication for at Least 75 Percent of Treatment Period: Ages 5-20
State Specific Comments: Medicaid rates include managed care population (4 MCOs), representing 85 percent of the population. Rates exclude FFS population, representing 15 percent of the population. Total rate includes children ages 5 to 18. MCO rates were audited by certified HEDIS auditors.
Source: Mathematica analysis of MACPro reports for the FFY 2017 reporting cycle as of November 1, 2018.

Domain: Primary Care Access and Preventive Care
Measure Name: Developmental Screening in the First Three Years of Life: Ages 0-3
Rate Definition: Percentage Screened for Risk of Developmental, Behavioral, and Social Delays Using a Standardized Screening Tool: Ages 0-3
State Specific Comments: CHIP rate includes FFS population. State reported data quality concerns resulting from a transition in its claims processing system, which resulted in a decrease in claims records for six months of the measurement period.
Source: Mathematica analysis of MACPro reports for the FFY 2017 reporting cycle as of November 1, 2018.

Domain: Primary Care Access and Preventive Care
Measure Name: Adolescent Well-Care Visits: Ages 12-21
Rate Definition: Percentage with at Least 1 Well-Care Visit with a Primary Care Practitioner or an Obstetrical/Gynecological Practitioner: Ages 12-21
State Specific Comments: CHIP rate includes managed care population (2 MCOs). Rate was derived using both administrative and hybrid method data. One MCO used the administrative method and one MCO used the hybrid method. Denominator is the measure-eligible population. MCO rates were audited by certified HEDIS auditors.
Source: Mathematica analysis of MACPro reports for the FFY 2017 reporting cycle as of November 1, 2018.

Domain: Primary Care Access and Preventive Care
Measure Name: Chlamydia Screening in Women Ages 16-20
Rate Definition: Percentage of Sexually Active Women Screened for Chlamydia: Ages 16-20
State Specific Comments: Medicaid rate includes managed care population (4 MCOs). Rate was validated by the state's EQRO.
Source: Mathematica analysis of MACPro reports for the FFY 2017 reporting cycle as of November 1, 2018.
